  "abstract": "The Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve System has issued an interpretation concerning the scope of the data processing provision of Regulation K. The interpretation clarifies that a banking organization may not engage in a broader range of data processing activities outside the United States under Regulation K than is permissible under Regulation Y, without the Board's approval.",
